summary: In this context, ethylbenzene and octane are both mentioned as part of a list of chemicals obtained for use in developing a sorbent packed needle trap (NT) device. They are categorized under BTEX (benzene, toluene, ethylbenzene, and o-xylene) and n-alkanes (including n-octane). However, there is no discussion of their specific interactions or functional relationships within the context of the study.
